                <exercise workspace="4in">
                    <title>Definition: Addition and Multiplication</title>
                    <statement>
                        <p>
                            <me>\overline{a} + \overline{b} := </me>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            <me>\overline{a} \cdot \overline{b} := </me>
                        </p>
                    </statement>
                    <solution>
                        <p>
                            <me>\overline{a} + \overline{b} := \overline{a+b} </me>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            <me>\overline{a} \cdot \overline{b} := \overline{a \cdot b} </me>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            This feels intuitive, but it's important to recognize that there is something to check here! 
                            See <url href="https://htmlpreview.github.io/?https://github.com/hulpke/csbook/blob/main/mathforcs.html#Ch2.S6.SS1">Section II.6 of our text</url> or our notes from class.
                        </p>
                    </solution>
                    
                </exercise>
